tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia and slightly low creatinine, which may reflect reduced muscle mass typical for advanced age. Other parameters, including renal function, electrolytes, calcium, and HbA1c, are within normal limits. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected; clinical correlation for hypoglycemia is recommended.
